Adds Discord bot support to the SDK and slightly reformats base notification message. Intentionally kept the message template light so that the bulk of it is defined by the Radio per the Radio's requirements.

I combined both Slack and Discord bots into one `bots.rs` file since I imagine a lot of the context around notifications in the future would be shared.

PS should be merged after https://github.com/graphops/poi-radio/pull/56 since the changes from there are merged in this branch for testing.

Example usage:
```
async fn main() {
    let discord_webhook_url = env::var("DISCORD_WEBHOOK_URL")
        .expect("Please set the DISCORD_WEBHOOK_URL environment variable");
    let slack_token = env::var("SLACK_TOKEN")
        .expect("Please set the SLACK_TOKEN environment variable");
    let slack_channel = env::var("SLACK_CHANNEL")
        .expect("Please set the SLACK_CHANNEL environment variable");

    let radio_name = "My Radio";
    let content = "This is an alert message";

    // Send a Discord notification
    match DiscordBot::send_webhook(&discord_webhook_url, radio_name, content).await {
        Ok(_) => println!("Discord notification sent successfully!"),
        Err(e) => eprintln!("Error sending Discord notification: {}", e),
    }

    // Send a Slack notification
    match SlackBot::send_webhook(slack_token, &slack_channel, radio_name, content).await {
        Ok(_) => println!("Slack notification sent successfully!"),
        Err(e) => eprintln!("Error sending Slack notification: {}", e),
    }
}
```
